description: There's double the danger as the chase brings Charles and Anna face-to-face with two rogue werewolves stalking the wilderness! And one of the monsters is controlled by a scheming sorceress who has plotted her attack for centuries. Can even an alpha wolf like Charles stand against their combined fury? Or does the key lie in the mysterious powers that omega wolf Anna has barely begun to explore?
name: Shattered Dreams

volume.name: Patricia Briggs' Alpha and Omega: Cry Wolf

description: Welcome to Neverland, an enclave of children who have survived the zombie apocalypse, apparently without any adult supervision whatsoever. What dark secret do they hold? Meanwhile, Russo and Diaz grow closer, and Doctor Federman’s suspicions about Ian deepen, despite the fact that he seems to have recuperated.

After last issue's fierce battle against a group of Innistrad vampires, Dack Fayden has found a new ally: young cathar Ingrid Reichert. With her help, Dack continues to track down the person who devastated his hometown. But when Dack stumbles into another vampire attack, even Ingrid's help may not be enough to get them out alive...

Unspeakable madness seeps out of the portal Cobra has opened, and it threatens to take over the entire Cobra base... and then spread across the globe! The only hope for survival lies in an unusual alliance between Snake Eyes and master-of-the-occult Crystal Ball. And who knows what role Storm Shadow will play! Pulse pounding horror excitement awaits!

THE PREQUEL TO THIS SUMMER’S MOST ANTICIPATED MOVIE STRIKES AGAIN! Snake Eyes—a deadly ninja. Roadblock—an unparalleled commando. Now’s the time for them to match skills and throw down. Who’ll win in this battle of fighting styles? It’s no holds barred brawling with the bad guys in the middle—plus, new secrets of Snake Eyes and Storm Shadow are revealed!

description:
Part Mad Max, part Escape from New York, Rebel is fast moving action oriented story that could have made a great movie. The year is 2003 and society as we know it has disintegrated. The cities are now vast wasteland where only crazies and rebels survive and fight over abandoned supermarkets. At the same time, USA has became a fascist state ruled by military thugs. Out of this mess comes out Rebel a lone fighter.

Set in New York city, the book uses photographs of actual landmarks. 60 pages full color, great work by the Spaniard Pepe Moreno.
name: Rebel

description: Welcome to the future that never was. After a devastating civil war, society as we knew it has ceased to exist. There are no “superpowers” and there are no superheroes either. Things are simple, everything is real and everything is lethal. There are no cell phones, no Internet and there's no 911. To survive you need guns (duh), and you must have wheels. It's the law of the jungle, it is raw, it is dangerous and it is out of control… And for some it's just fun…
name: Rebel

This rare import comes straight from Chos 2010 Paris exhibition. An impressive hardcover catalogue featuring 48 pages of pen and ink drawings and fully finished color work. By turns comedic and dramatic, this collection showcases Chos broad ranging talent from his early Liberty Meadows work through more recent oil paintings and Jungle Queens art. And as with all Cho books, the beauty of the female form prevails throughout. Only 1500 copies of the exhibit catalogue were printed.

In 1923, Nikola Tesla's career is in its twilight... until he unveils a robot with automatic intelligence - ATOMIC ROBO! After decades of dealing with all manner of weirdness, Atomic Robo and the so-called Action Scientists of Tesladyne become the go-to defense force against the unexplained! See ROBO take on Nazis, giant ants, clockwork mummies, walking pyramids, Mars, cyborgs, and his nemesis, Baron von Helsingard.

Collects Atomic Robo #1-6.
